President Donald J. Trump has announced several appointments for the Executive Office of the President. Hogan Gidley will serve as Deputy Assistant to the President and Principal Deputy Press Secretary, focusing on issues related to the Department of Defense, Department of Homeland Security, and the Department of State. Lindsay Walters will continue to serve as Special Assistant to the President and Deputy Press Secretary, focusing on issues related to various departments including the Department of Commerce, Office of the United States Trade Representative, and Department of the Treasury. Judd Deere will serve as Special Assistant to the President and Deputy Press Secretary, focusing on issues related to various departments including the Department of Housing and Urban Development and Department of Agriculture. Steven Groves will serve as Special Assistant to the President and Deputy Press Secretary, focusing on issues related to legislative affairs, oversight, nominees, and the Department of Justice.